WEBVTT

00:02.736 --> 00:04.705
(CLATTERING)

00:08.242 --> 00:09.577
(GLASS CLINKING)

00:09.643 --> 00:11.779
Good morning.

00:11.845 --> 00:14.014
Morning.
(CLEARS THROAT)

00:15.816 --> 00:17.751
I'm Jake,
we met last week.

00:17.818 --> 00:20.321
Yes, we did.

00:21.422 --> 00:23.924
I was just
gonna get some juice.

00:23.991 --> 00:26.360
Hope you don't mind.
Are you a drummer?

00:26.427 --> 00:30.064
Am I a drummer?
No. No, I'm a chef.

00:30.131 --> 00:31.665
Well, actually,
just a cook, but...

00:31.732 --> 00:33.134
Lea dates drummers.

00:35.035 --> 00:38.139
I played clarinet
in junior high.

00:38.206 --> 00:39.807
Hmm.

00:39.873 --> 00:42.243
(DOOR OPENS)

00:42.310 --> 00:43.711
**

00:43.777 --> 00:45.579
LEA: What are you
doing out here?

00:45.646 --> 00:46.947
I told you
to stay in my room.

00:47.014 --> 00:49.617
I just snuck out
to grab some O.J.

00:49.683 --> 00:51.085
Mmm-hmm.

00:51.152 --> 00:53.921
I was really thirsty.
Okay.

00:53.987 --> 00:56.124
**

00:58.826 --> 00:59.960
(DOOR CLOSES)

01:00.561 --> 01:01.895
I'm sorry.

01:01.962 --> 01:04.098
I should've told you
he was spending the night.

01:04.165 --> 01:05.399
I like Jake.

01:07.535 --> 01:10.070
That's nice
of you to say.

01:10.138 --> 01:12.906
I know it's difficult
to have a stranger
in your home.

01:12.973 --> 01:17.278
I have to drive Dr. Glassman
to his chemo appointment.

01:17.345 --> 01:20.281
He's five days in
and doing very well.

01:20.348 --> 01:22.116
I'm helping him.

01:22.183 --> 01:24.285
Jake is very sweet.

01:24.352 --> 01:26.120
You know,
when you get to know him,

01:26.187 --> 01:27.655
I'm sure you really
will like him.

01:27.721 --> 01:29.623
I said I like him.

01:29.690 --> 01:31.792
Will he be spending
the night here a lot now?

01:31.859 --> 01:33.026
No, not a lot.

01:35.062 --> 01:36.330
But...

01:36.397 --> 01:38.366
Would that
be a problem?

01:38.432 --> 01:40.834
No.
So is it cool

01:40.901 --> 01:42.770
if I have him over tonight
to watch a movie?

01:44.238 --> 01:45.506
It's cool.

01:47.040 --> 01:49.177
I have to go.

01:53.281 --> 01:55.949
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

01:56.016 --> 01:57.985
(COUGHS)

01:58.051 --> 02:00.588
**

02:02.723 --> 02:06.059
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

02:07.928 --> 02:09.797
SHAUN: (DISTANT)
Good morning, Dr. Glassman.

02:11.532 --> 02:14.067
I let myself in.
I'm downstairs.

02:15.636 --> 02:16.637
(SIGHS)

02:44.232 --> 02:46.600
How are you
feeling today?

02:46.667 --> 02:49.970
Good, actually.
Better than yesterday.

02:50.037 --> 02:52.573
Yes, your skin was
a bit pale yesterday.

02:52.640 --> 02:54.575
Today your color
looks much better.

02:54.642 --> 02:56.310
I brought you
your electrolytes.

02:57.345 --> 02:59.012
Thank you.

02:59.079 --> 03:00.648
Cheers.

03:02.516 --> 03:03.784
(GAGS)

03:08.322 --> 03:10.558
(COUGHING)

03:10.624 --> 03:12.059
Why did you do that?

03:12.125 --> 03:13.427
(SIGHS)

03:13.494 --> 03:15.128
I don't like the flavor,
the grape.

03:15.195 --> 03:16.630
Are you
experiencing nausea?

03:16.697 --> 03:19.132
No, I didn't
like the flavor,
I told you.

03:21.302 --> 03:22.636
I'm fine.

03:22.703 --> 03:23.837
(BOTTLE THUDS)

03:26.340 --> 03:27.808
I'm glad
you're feeling well.

03:27.875 --> 03:30.778
Let's go,
or we're going to be late.

03:30.844 --> 03:34.282
Yep. Cancer's not
gonna kill itself.

03:34.348 --> 03:35.949
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

03:36.016 --> 03:37.751
(BEEP)

03:37.818 --> 03:39.587
Hey.

03:39.653 --> 03:41.389
I was just
thinking about you, too.

03:42.856 --> 03:44.458
Actually, can I
call you at lunch?

03:44.525 --> 03:45.759
I'm with some people
right now, and...

03:45.826 --> 03:48.796
(CHUCKLES)
Yes, exactly.

03:48.862 --> 03:50.964
We'll talk later.

03:51.031 --> 03:52.533
Love you.

03:54.234 --> 03:55.869
(BEEP)

03:59.707 --> 04:01.208
New girlfriend?

04:02.576 --> 04:05.746
Still in the call-each-other-
the-next-morning phase?

04:05.813 --> 04:07.348
Yeah, you got me.

04:09.883 --> 04:11.952
Actually, no.
It was Mia.

04:12.019 --> 04:13.954
We're giving our
relationship
another shot.

04:14.021 --> 04:16.824
Wow. Park,
that's great.

04:16.890 --> 04:21.429
Yeah, I told you because part
of the thing with Mia is...

04:21.495 --> 04:23.196
I'm trying
to be more open.

04:24.732 --> 04:27.301
Thanks. You didn't
need to explain,

04:27.368 --> 04:29.303
but sounds good.

04:29.370 --> 04:31.204
She sounds like
she's good for you.

04:33.374 --> 04:35.309
Yeah.

04:35.376 --> 04:36.610
Of course,
if it doesn't work out,

04:36.677 --> 04:37.945
I'll have to talk to you
about that, too,

04:38.011 --> 04:39.947
admit I failed.
(CHUCKLES)

04:40.013 --> 04:41.882
Or I can be
a supportive colleague

04:41.949 --> 04:43.717
regardless
of what happens.

04:45.919 --> 04:48.856
(CELL PHONE CHIMES)
(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)

04:50.090 --> 04:52.292
**

04:52.360 --> 04:56.364
Seventy-year-old female.
Neighbor saw her collapse
in her yard.

04:56.430 --> 04:59.333
Unresponsive.
No heartbeat.
EKG is flatlined.

04:59.400 --> 05:01.702
Then she'd be cyanotic.

05:01.769 --> 05:03.704
Good capillary refill...
She's perfusing?

05:03.771 --> 05:05.305
Stop CPR.

05:05.373 --> 05:07.508
And she's breathing.
Your EKG must be broken.

05:07.575 --> 05:09.309
Worked fine on our call
right before her.

05:09.377 --> 05:11.211
Everything works fine
up until it doesn't.

05:11.278 --> 05:12.780
**

05:13.714 --> 05:16.049
Nothing.
Told you.

05:16.116 --> 05:17.985
Hook her up,
let's check her vitals.

05:19.953 --> 05:22.022
Blood is definitely flowing
to her extremities.

05:22.089 --> 05:23.624
(FLATLINE)

05:31.932 --> 05:33.901
Should we push epi,
get the crash...

05:33.967 --> 05:35.936
Wait. Everyone quiet.

05:36.003 --> 05:37.070
(CLICK)

05:37.137 --> 05:38.572
(FLATLINE STOPS)

05:44.512 --> 05:45.746
Listen.

05:47.080 --> 05:48.516
(WHIRRING)

05:51.452 --> 05:52.453
Is that...?

05:55.923 --> 05:58.692
(WHIRRING CONTINUES)

05:58.759 --> 06:01.695
She doesn't have a rhythm
because she has
a mechanical heart.

06:02.463 --> 06:04.465
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

06:12.540 --> 06:14.875
Lana Moore.
34-year-old female,

06:14.942 --> 06:17.077
was slurring her words,
symptom passed,

06:17.144 --> 06:19.947
but we found a grade two
arteriovenous malformation
in her brain.

06:20.013 --> 06:23.717
Are we going to do
endovascular embolization

06:23.784 --> 06:26.720
or stereotactic radiosurgery
or resection?

06:26.787 --> 06:28.489
Endovascular embolization.

06:28.556 --> 06:30.924
Patient requests she's only
served green jello

06:30.991 --> 06:32.926
and that we dim all of
our incandescent light bulbs?

06:32.993 --> 06:35.295
Lana has autism.

06:35.362 --> 06:36.730
What're you
looking at him for?

06:36.797 --> 06:38.298
It's not like
they all know each other.

06:38.365 --> 06:40.100
I was just curious
what his thoughts might be.

06:40.167 --> 06:42.903
I think we should go with
endovascular embolization.

06:42.970 --> 06:44.505
Hmm. Now you know.

06:44.572 --> 06:46.974
The AVM is dangerous,
but the embolization

06:47.040 --> 06:48.809
is a relatively
minor procedure.

06:48.876 --> 06:50.944
We'll make a small incision
in your leg

06:51.011 --> 06:52.312
so we can insert
a catheter into your...

06:52.379 --> 06:53.514
Are you okay, Javi?

06:54.682 --> 06:56.416
The lights aren't
bothering you too much?

06:57.485 --> 06:58.686
A little.

07:10.263 --> 07:11.899
Please continue.

07:13.200 --> 07:16.136
We'll insert the catheter
into your femoral artery.

07:16.203 --> 07:18.371
Then we'll feed it up
into the arteriovenous
malform...

07:18.438 --> 07:20.307
You brought a dictionary?

07:20.373 --> 07:22.009
Uh, is there something
I'm saying

07:22.075 --> 07:24.478
that you don't understand?
Lana loves learning new words.

07:24.545 --> 07:26.113
She's memorized
the scientific Latin name

07:26.179 --> 07:27.815
of every bug in South America.

07:27.881 --> 07:31.519
Go ahead, name any
six-legged critter.
I love being quizzed.

07:33.453 --> 07:36.857
(CHUCKLES)
Rhinoceros Beetle.

07:36.924 --> 07:39.459
Megasoma actaeon.
Found in Guyana.

07:39.527 --> 07:40.994
It's the heaviest insect
in the world

07:41.061 --> 07:43.396
and weighs as much
as 300 grasshoppers.

07:45.098 --> 07:46.299
Is she right?

07:47.400 --> 07:48.602
I have no idea.

07:49.737 --> 07:50.738
I have to go.

07:55.208 --> 07:57.010
Javi...

07:57.077 --> 07:58.411
Javi.

07:59.079 --> 08:00.848
Where are you going?

08:00.914 --> 08:02.850
It's 11:15.
I have to be
home by noon

08:02.916 --> 08:04.317
to watch Judge Judy
before work.

08:04.384 --> 08:05.719
I-It's important to us

08:05.786 --> 08:07.354
that your girlfriend
doesn't get stressed out,

08:07.420 --> 08:11.725
so we'd prefer it
if you stayed with her
as long as you can.

08:11.792 --> 08:14.161
Lana's not my girlfriend.
We're just roommates.

08:19.733 --> 08:21.434
(WHIRRING)

08:21.501 --> 08:23.170
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

08:23.236 --> 08:24.905
Still stable?

08:24.972 --> 08:26.707
The diuretics have
her O2 SATs up,

08:26.774 --> 08:28.508
but she's hypotensive.
And we checked every center

08:28.576 --> 08:30.277
approved to implant
mechanical hearts,

08:30.343 --> 08:32.212
but none have any record
of her as a patient.

08:32.279 --> 08:33.714
Check overseas.
I'd start with...

08:33.781 --> 08:34.848
Mom?

08:36.316 --> 08:37.450
Is it her heart?

08:37.517 --> 08:39.887
The implanted device
appears to be malfunctioning.

08:39.953 --> 08:41.354
Do you have
any contact information

08:41.421 --> 08:42.623
for the surgeon
who implanted it?

08:42.690 --> 08:43.857
Yes, of course.

08:44.692 --> 08:47.394
Dr. Li Wei.
He's in Beijing.

08:47.460 --> 08:48.762
When did she
have it implanted?

08:50.163 --> 08:51.398
A little
over nine months.

08:53.033 --> 08:55.002
She just went back

08:55.068 --> 08:56.570
for a follow-up exam
last month.

08:56.637 --> 08:57.705
She was fine.

08:59.873 --> 09:00.974
Can you fix it?

09:01.809 --> 09:03.243
I'm gonna find out.

09:04.544 --> 09:06.847
**

09:13.153 --> 09:14.387
Hello.

09:15.723 --> 09:17.190
Hello.

09:22.696 --> 09:23.964
Don't be stupid.

09:24.031 --> 09:25.398
What? There's no cameras
in here.

09:26.199 --> 09:27.534
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

09:29.202 --> 09:31.739
Dr. Lim, Dr. Melendez.

09:31.805 --> 09:33.741
How was your
respective weekends?

09:33.807 --> 09:35.809
Good.
Checked out some bikes.

09:35.876 --> 09:38.078
Brushed up on
some reading.
Excellent.

09:38.145 --> 09:40.113
I hear the search for
Chief of Surgery is back on.

09:40.180 --> 09:41.915
As is our legal
department's response

09:41.982 --> 09:43.450
to the DPH complaint
against both of you,

09:43.516 --> 09:45.318
so I wouldn't
get your hopes up.

09:45.385 --> 09:46.854
Probably just as well.

09:46.920 --> 09:49.122
I'd rather not see the two
of you competing again.

09:49.189 --> 09:50.824
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

09:50.891 --> 09:53.160
You seem to be getting
along better.

09:53.226 --> 09:55.629
**

09:58.198 --> 10:00.200
(WHIRRING)

10:01.869 --> 10:03.336
(CLANGING)

10:03.403 --> 10:04.738
DR. REZNICK: It's weird.

10:06.406 --> 10:07.875
Is it weird?

10:07.941 --> 10:09.843
They act like a couple,
right?

10:09.910 --> 10:12.145
I live with Lea,
but we're not a couple.

10:12.212 --> 10:14.014
Yeah,
but you wish you were.

10:16.684 --> 10:17.651
Do you?

10:18.385 --> 10:20.721
Lea has a new boyfriend.

10:20.788 --> 10:22.956
You must be
a little jealous.

10:24.557 --> 10:25.993
Why?

10:26.059 --> 10:28.528
Lea's my friend
and Lea's happy.

10:29.897 --> 10:30.931
Okay.

10:30.998 --> 10:34.267
Jake, Lea, and I can
all be friends together.

10:34.334 --> 10:36.036
(KEYS CLACKING)

10:36.103 --> 10:38.806
Shaun, Lea's new boyfriend
doesn't want to hang out
with the three of you.

10:39.773 --> 10:41.474
If Lea really
likes this guy,

10:41.541 --> 10:43.643
she's gonna want to
spend time just with him.

10:44.978 --> 10:46.213
I know.

10:46.279 --> 10:47.547
For the sex.

10:47.614 --> 10:49.016
(BEEP)

10:52.385 --> 10:55.022
Her AVM
has microbleeds.

10:55.088 --> 10:57.157
Her risk of rupture
is doubled.

10:57.224 --> 10:59.159
**

11:01.795 --> 11:03.931
(BEIJING NURSE
SPEAKING MANDARIN OVER PHONE)

11:03.997 --> 11:05.432
They paged
Sunny's surgeon.

11:05.498 --> 11:06.900
He's gonna call you
in an hour.

11:06.967 --> 11:08.201
Tell them
I can't wait that long.

11:08.268 --> 11:09.569
Her cardiac output
is low and...
Got it.

11:09.636 --> 11:11.839
(SPEAKING MANDARIN)

11:21.014 --> 11:24.417
(BEIJING NURSE
SPEAKING MANDARIN)

11:24.484 --> 11:25.819
He's in surgery.

11:28.488 --> 11:30.657
Excuse me.
Uh, Dr. Melendez?

11:30.724 --> 11:32.926
I'm Grace Lee.
Sunny Lee's daughter.

11:32.993 --> 11:35.863
They told me downstairs
that you're
my mother's doctor.

11:35.929 --> 11:37.965
DR. MELENDEZ: Yes.
Get them to send her records

11:38.031 --> 11:39.466
and everything they can
about the device.

11:39.532 --> 11:41.334
Manufacturer,
model number, manuals.

11:43.003 --> 11:44.805
Your mother's stable,
but we're struggling

11:44.872 --> 11:47.808
to get the information we need
from her doctor in China.

11:47.875 --> 11:49.642
I don't understand.
Her doctor's in China?

11:49.709 --> 11:51.378
Like on vacation?

11:51.444 --> 11:53.981
No, her cardiac surgeon.

11:54.047 --> 11:56.549
Your sister can fill
you in on everything
we've done so far.

11:56.616 --> 11:59.152
I really need to get back
on this phone call.
Wait.

11:59.219 --> 12:00.988
I don't have a sister.

12:03.090 --> 12:05.993
**

12:11.765 --> 12:14.701
We met 10 years ago
while I was volunteering
at a senior center.

12:15.535 --> 12:16.970
We hit it off.

12:17.037 --> 12:19.306
Neither of us had anyone
in our lives at the time.

12:21.574 --> 12:23.076
People assumed we were
mother and daughter

12:23.143 --> 12:25.612
because we did
everything together.

12:25.678 --> 12:27.314
After a while,
we just went with it.

12:29.249 --> 12:31.118
She'll be glad
to see you.

12:31.184 --> 12:33.186
You look like you've put
your problems behind you.

12:33.921 --> 12:35.055
Problems?

12:35.122 --> 12:36.689
She told me about
your issues with drugs.

12:39.526 --> 12:41.628
Oh, my God.

12:41.694 --> 12:43.864
She caught me
smoking pot.

12:43.931 --> 12:46.233
Once.
I was a teenager.

12:46.299 --> 12:49.669
So you're fine?
Of course I'm fine.

12:49.736 --> 12:51.171
Then you don't
really have an excuse

12:51.238 --> 12:53.540
for not calling
for 15 years,
do you?

12:58.111 --> 12:59.279
DR. MELENDEZ:
They want her back.

12:59.346 --> 13:00.513
They've arranged
for transport...

13:00.580 --> 13:01.949
They'll do
the repairs in Beijing.

13:02.015 --> 13:03.516
Is that safe?

13:03.583 --> 13:05.352
Can she travel for that long
in her condition?

13:05.418 --> 13:06.820
It's a specially-equipped
plane for patients

13:06.887 --> 13:08.688
requiring urgent
medical assistance.

13:08.755 --> 13:10.357
And 20 hours in the air
is much safer

13:10.423 --> 13:12.392
than at least that long
on an operating table here

13:12.459 --> 13:13.760
while we basically
fly blind.

13:13.827 --> 13:14.962
Okay.
Okay.

13:18.398 --> 13:20.133
Prep her
for transport.

13:21.134 --> 13:23.703
**

13:29.276 --> 13:30.911
(SIGHS)

13:30.978 --> 13:32.913
DR. REZNICK:
The microbleeds indicate

13:32.980 --> 13:34.848
that it may already
be starting to rupture.

13:34.915 --> 13:38.318
If it goes, you could suffer
permanent brain damage
or death.

13:38.385 --> 13:41.721
Because of that,
embolization is no longer
our preferred approach.

13:41.788 --> 13:43.756
We want to open you up
and cut it out.

13:47.060 --> 13:49.029
Can you try
talking to her?

13:49.096 --> 13:50.998
Just because
I have autism doesn't...

13:51.064 --> 13:52.732
I'm not asking you
because you have autism.

13:52.799 --> 13:54.567
I'm asking you because
you're her doctor

13:54.634 --> 13:56.503
and I'm getting
nowhere.

14:09.917 --> 14:12.852
The sting of
the Japanese Giant Hornet

14:12.920 --> 14:15.588
can dissolve human flesh
and attack the nervous system.

14:15.655 --> 14:19.226
Recommended treatment
includes oral antihistamine
and acetaminophen.

14:24.097 --> 14:25.332
Comforting
choice of words.

14:31.138 --> 14:33.040
(PAPER RUSTLING)

14:36.509 --> 14:38.578
It's 6:30. Dinner time.

14:38.645 --> 14:41.048
I brought burgers and jello.
This one's yours.

14:41.114 --> 14:42.649
Lana can't eat now.

14:42.715 --> 14:44.351
We're trying to schedule
a surgery to...

14:44.417 --> 14:45.518
I could die.

14:48.155 --> 14:52.692
The surgery sounds scary
but necessary, so I'll do it.

14:52.759 --> 14:55.428
**

14:57.464 --> 14:59.632
"...big feet got there first.
Johnny stumbled caught himself

14:59.699 --> 15:01.034
"and swung silently
about at Dove.

15:01.101 --> 15:02.702
"'Gosh, Johnny, I'm sorry,'
snickered Dove.

15:02.769 --> 15:04.304
"'Sorry, eh, you're going
to be a lot sorrier.'

15:04.371 --> 15:05.939
"'I just didn't notice.'
'You do that a...'"
Shaun.

15:06.006 --> 15:07.107
What are you doing?

15:07.174 --> 15:09.142
Reading to you
from Johnny Tremain.

15:09.209 --> 15:11.344
You're reading words.
You're not reading sentences.

15:11.411 --> 15:15.148
This edition of
Johnny Tremain
is 320 pages long.

15:15.215 --> 15:16.349
To get through
the entire thing,

15:16.416 --> 15:18.585
I need to read 270 words
per minute.

15:18.651 --> 15:21.354
You don't have to finish
the book in one sitting.

15:21.421 --> 15:22.956
Oh, yes,
that's how I read novels.

15:23.023 --> 15:24.992
I want to know
where the characters end up.

15:25.058 --> 15:26.226
You know what?
Let's just stop.

15:27.094 --> 15:28.595
I can go slower.

15:28.661 --> 15:31.298
I-I'm not listening, anyway.
Are you in pain?

15:31.364 --> 15:33.166
No, no, I'm not...
You seem fatigued.

15:33.233 --> 15:35.368
You know what?
I have a good idea.

15:35.435 --> 15:37.370
Why don't you
take out the garbage?

15:45.445 --> 15:46.613
Thank you.

15:48.381 --> 15:50.717
(SIGHS)

15:50.783 --> 15:52.119
Where is
your recycling?

15:52.185 --> 15:53.320
